Blueberry Muffins (from Joy of Cooking)

1 3/4 cups flour
3/4 tsp salt
1/3 cup sugar
2 tsp baking powder
2 eggs
1/4 cup melted butter
3/4 cup milk
1 cup fresh blueberries
(optional: some vanilla)
(optional: poppyseeds)

Mix dry ingredients.

Mix eggs, butter and milk (and vanilla and poppyseeds) and add to dry ingredients with a few
swift strokes.

Fill cupcake papers in muffin tins about 2/3 full and bake at 350-400 degrees
for about 20 minutes.

Makes one dozen.
